    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01684_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#unk" place="top">(1885)</note>
            <!--Probably an archival note-->
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date>Wednesday <choice><abbr>Evn'g</abbr><expan>evening</expan></choice></date>
                    <date when="1885-05-13">May 13</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p> Aleck dear boy I cannot find "Locusts &amp; Wild Honey" this moment&#8212;but let
                me lend you another of John Burroughs's<ptr target="n0129"/> books&#8212;(thought by some to be his
                best.)&#8212;"Birds and Poets"&#8212;hope it will please you &amp; your mother and
                sister. </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Your friend</salute>
                <signed>W W</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Aleck boy here is a copy slip of my little new poem just out in <hi
                    rend="underline">Harpers' Weekly</hi> of May 16.<ptr target="loc.07000_n2"/></p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01685_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
